The differences between financial and managerial accounting. The areas of management accounting. The basics of cost classification. Accounting information for decision making. Traditional and contemporary costing methods. Companies' planning and budgeting. Internal reporting. Responsibility accounting. Management control. Performance measurement and performance management. Balanced Scorecard. Sustainability reporting and management. Financial statement analysis methods - horizontal, vertical and ratio analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course covers basic design issues of management accounting system's main elements - cost accounting, planning and reporting - and their use in decision-making, planning and control. The course also emphasizes the analysis and interpretation of financial statement information to better understand the role of management accounting on transparency of company performance and financial conditions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student taking the course will understand: 1)	principles of the cost accounting system, the planning and internal reporting system of the companies; 2)	elements of the cost system, cost objects and cost centres; 3)	the costing methods and to use them; 4)	how to use cost information in decision making; 5)	the master budget and to develop the master budget; 6)	the companies' internal reporting principles; 7)     the performance measurement principles and methods, e.g. balanced scorecard;  8)	the financial statement analysis methods; 9)     the concept of sustainability reporting and management;  10)	the role of management accounting on company performance and financial conditions
